<Layout title="ShoeCarnival.com">
  <p>
    Shoe Carnival, one of the nation’s largest family footwear retailers, offers
    a broad assortment of dress, casual, and athletic brand name footwear for
    men, women, and children.
  </p><p>
    With 80% of the retailer’s traffic coming from mobile and a proprietary
    front end that was both slow and challenging to develop, Shoe Carnival was
    looking for a proper solution.
  </p>
  <h2>Project Goals</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Develop mobile version of retail site using existing desktop-oriented site
      as a backend
    </li>
    <li>
      Setup Layer0 network for splitting traffic between mobile and basic verion
    </li>
    <li>Speed up the mobile site as much as possible</li>
    <li>Add automatically generated interactive AMP version of pages</li>
    <li>
      Get green statuses on PageSpeed Insights for all retail pages (landings /
      product lists / product details)
    </li>
    <li>
      Integrate analytics without negative affects on page load speed and
      metrics
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>My Participation</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Leading client kickoff phase</li>
    <li>Team Lead</li>
    <li>Develop network architecture</li>
    <li>Manage roll-outs and releases</li>
    <li>Client communication</li>
    <li>Co-piloting PM's</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Results</h2>
  <figure>
    <blockquote cite="https://edg.io/resources/case-study/shoe-carnival/">
      “On Layer0, we have better speed and conversions. From a developer’s
      standpoint, we have far more flexibility and no restrictions.”
    </blockquote>
    <figcaption>
      <p>Tyler Drone, Sr. Manager of Digital Development - Shoe Carnival</p>
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <figure>
    <img
      src="/img/projects/shoecarnival-com.png"
      alt="ShoeCarnival.com PLP to PDP transition"
    />
    <figcaption>
      Improve <dfn title="Product List Page">PLP</dfn> to <dfn
        title="Product Details Page">PDP</dfn
      > transition from 6&thinsp;sec. to 0.5&thinsp;sec.
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>We released with 3 months delay the project and achieved:</p>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-1of2">
      <h3>Speed</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>320ms median page loads (LCP)</li>
        <li>
          92% reduction in browsing transitions dropping from 6 seconds to 500ms
        </li>
        <li>
          70.5% increase in first load speeds dropping from 3.4 seconds to 1
          second
        </li>
        <li>67% increase in first-load speeds in total</li>
        <li>
          <dfn
            title="It means we cache everything except user-related data of the site"
            >95%+ cache hit rate</dfn
          > for dynamic content at the edge
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-1of2">
      <h3>Traffic</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>32%+ average organic traffic growth</li>
        <li>
          Outperforms 98% of websites and outranks Amazon, Zappos, Nordstrom
          Sales
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Sales</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>10B+ in revenue flows through Layer0 a year</li>
        <li>48% lift in organic conversion rate</li>
        <li>40% lift in overall revenue with a sub-second website</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
